<subSubSection id="DBF56570FFB1FFF54594467AFB0AFAA2" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="1603" pageId="1" pageNumber="1600" type="description">
<paragraph id="935036FBFFB1FFF34594467AFDB3F904" blockId="1.[144,1104,1316,1691]" lastBlockId="2.[212,1172,1411,1690]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="1601" pageId="1" pageNumber="1600">
The recognition of 
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB1FFF0448F467CFDA8F9A5" baseAuthorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[419,561,1572,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="1600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB1FFF0448F467CFDA8F9A5" box="[419,561,1572,1596]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="1600">M. crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has proved troublesome from the beginning. 
<bibRefCitation id="F77E4B0AFFB1FFF045BC461AFED5F9C5" author="Lundbeck W" box="[144,332,1603,1627]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1600" refId="ref8487" refString="Lundbeck W. 1922. Diptera Danica Part VI Pipunculidae, Phoridae. London: Wesley." type="book" year="1922">Lundbeck (1922)</bibRefCitation>
only included Woodâ€™ s species in his key to the species of his Group IV. However, he included his 
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB1FFF044FB463DFC88F9E2" box="[471,785,1636,1660]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="1600">
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB1FFF044FB463DFDFAF9E2" authorityName="Lundbeck" authorityYear="1920" box="[471,611,1636,1660]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Aphiochaeta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="1600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dactylata">M. dactylata</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB1FFF047B5463DFC88F9E2" authorityName="Lundbeck" authorityYear="1921" box="[665,785,1636,1660]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Aphiochaeta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="1600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exclusa">M. exclusa</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
in both the key and the text. Subsequently, 
<bibRefCitation id="F77E4B0AFFB1FFF0441E46DAFE40F905" author="Schmitz H" box="[306,473,1667,1691]" pageId="1" pageNumber="1600" pagination="350 - 379" refId="ref8553" refString="Schmitz H. 1952. Uber W. Lundbecks Sammlung und Beschreibung Danischer Phoriden. Entomologiske Meddelelser. 26: 350 - 379." type="journal article" year="1952">Schmitz (1952)</bibRefCitation>
synonymised both these species with 
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB1FFF046A546DDFB82F905" box="[905,1051,1668,1691]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="1600">
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB1FFF046A546DDFB8EF905" baseAuthorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[905,1047,1668,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="1600" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">M. crassipes</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The effect of this was to play havoc with Lundbeckâ€™ s key to his Group IV. For example, his first couplet separates those species with long costal cilia from those in which they are short. It is evident, however, that these cilia vary across accepted conventions regarding the boundary between â€˜shortâ€™ and â€˜longâ€™. The failure to appreciate this caused 
<bibRefCitation id="F77E4B0AFFB2FFF3411045BBFE81F984" author="Schmitz H" pageId="2" pageNumber="1601" pagination="465 - 512" refId="ref8577" refString="Schmitz H. 1958. Phoridae. In: Lindner E, editor. Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region 4 (33) (Lieferung 202). Stuttgart: E. Schweizerbart' sche Verlagsbuchhandlung; p. 465 - 512." type="book chapter" year="1958">Schmitz (1958)</bibRefCitation>
to key out this species in his Abteilung IV, Erste Reuhe. 
<bibRefCitation id="F77E4B0AFFB2FFF34652465BFB0DF984" author="Schmitz H &amp; Beyer E" box="[894,1172,1538,1563]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1601" pagination="513 - 608" refId="ref8619" refString="Schmitz H, Beyer E. 1965. Phoridae. In: Lindner E editor. Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region 4 (33) (Lieferung 258, 260). Stuttgart: E. Schweizerbart' sche Verlagsbuchhandlung; p. 513 - 608." type="book chapter" year="1965">Schmitz and Beyer (1965)</bibRefCitation>
then keyed out 
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB2FFF344AD467AFD31F9A4" authority="in Abteilung" authorityName="in Abteilung" box="[385,680,1570,1594]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1601" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gargarans">
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB2FFF344AD467AFD8FF9A4" box="[385,534,1571,1594]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1601">M. gargarans</emphasis>
in Abteilung
</taxonomicName>
IV, Zweite Reihe. To add to the confusion, 
<bibRefCitation id="F77E4B0AFFB2FFF345F8461BFE09F9C4" author="Borgmeier T" box="[212,400,1602,1626]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1601" pagination="1 - 367" refId="ref7815" refString="Borgmeier T. 1968. A catalogue of the Phoridae of the world (Diptera, Phoridae). Studia Entomologica, Petropolis. 11: 1 - 367." type="journal article" year="1968">Borgmeier (1968)</bibRefCitation>
cited the wrong paper of Schmitz for the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB2FFF346F5461AFBFAF9C4" authorityName="Lundbeck" authorityYear="1920" box="[985,1123,1602,1626]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Aphiochaeta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1601" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dactylata">
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB2FFF346F5461AFBFAF9C4" box="[985,1123,1602,1626]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1601">M. dactylata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but correctly observed that 
<bibRefCitation id="F77E4B0AFFB2FFF344F4463BFDE5F9E4" author="Schmitz H" box="[472,636,1634,1658]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1601" pagination="465 - 512" refId="ref8577" refString="Schmitz H. 1958. Phoridae. In: Lindner E, editor. Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region 4 (33) (Lieferung 202). Stuttgart: E. Schweizerbart' sche Verlagsbuchhandlung; p. 465 - 512." type="book chapter" year="1958">Schmitz (1958)</bibRefCitation>
had erroneously referred a photo of the wing of another species to 
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB2FFF344B146DAFDB3F904" box="[413,554,1667,1690]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1601">
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB2FFF344B146DAFDBFF904" baseAuthorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[413,550,1667,1690]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1601" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">M. crassipes</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<caption id="C7906673FFB2FFF345F8454BFE6EFADB" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4006316" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4006316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4006316/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1601" startId="2.[212,279,1298,1320]" targetBox="[213,1171,169,1265]" targetPageId="2">
