<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB2FFF34412454BFD9CFAB9" baseAuthorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[318,517,1298,1319]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="1601" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB2FFF34412454BFD9CFAB9" box="[318,517,1298,1319]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1601">Megaselia crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
male. (A) Posterior face of front tarsus; (B) left face of hypopytgium. Scale bar: 0.1 mm.
