<paragraph id="935036FBFFB3FFF5459444FBFB0AFAA2" blockId="3.[144,1104,1186,1689]" lastBlockId="4.[212,1172,1284,1340]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="1603" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602">
The recognition of 
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB3FFF244BF44FAFDB3FB24" box="[403,554,1187,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gargarans">
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB3FFF244BF44FAFDB3FB24" box="[403,554,1187,1210]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602">M. gargarans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has also proved troublesome. In the keys to the males of the species of the British Isles (
<bibRefCitation id="F77E4B0AFFB3FFF2471F449BFD22FB44" author="Disney RHL" box="[563,699,1218,1242]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602" pagination="1 - 155" refId="ref8043" refString="Disney RHL. 1989. Scuttle Flies - Diptera Phoridae Genus Megaselia. Handbk Ident Br Insects. 10: 1 - 155." type="journal article" year="1989">Disney 1989</bibRefCitation>
), it seemingly runs to couplet 81, lead 2, to 
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB3FFF245EB44BAFED4FB64" baseAuthorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[199,333,1251,1274]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB3FFF245EB44BAFED4FB64" box="[199,333,1251,1274]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602">M. crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Schmitz did not provide a figure of the hypopygium but described the anal tube as being â€˜kurz, kaum lÃ¤nger als hochâ€™, which would immediately exclude 
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB3FFF24102455AFF6EFAA4" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602">
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB3FFF24102455AFF6AFAA4" baseAuthorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">M. crassipes</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
In the keys of 
<bibRefCitation id="F77E4B0AFFB3FFF24489457BFD51FAA4" author="Schmitz H &amp; Beyer E" box="[421,712,1314,1339]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602" pagination="513 - 608" refId="ref8619" refString="Schmitz H, Beyer E. 1965. Phoridae. In: Lindner E editor. Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region 4 (33) (Lieferung 258, 260). Stuttgart: E. Schweizerbart' sche Verlagsbuchhandlung; p. 513 - 608." type="book chapter" year="1965">Schmitz and Beyer (1965)</bibRefCitation>
, the males of 
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB3FFF24646457AFB98FAA4" box="[874,1025,1315,1338]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gargarans">
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB3FFF24646457AFB98FAA4" box="[874,1025,1315,1338]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602">M. gargarans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
run to couplet 52 on p. 523. Furthermore, in the text Beyer pointed out that Schmitzâ€™ s description of the anal tube was incorrect, as he reported his measurement of its length-tobreadth ratio as being 8:4. Examination of Schmitzâ€™ s slide mount of a 
<typeStatus id="4C548859FFB3FFF246B945DBFC6FFA04" box="[917,1014,1410,1434]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602">paratype</typeStatus>
male of 
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB3FFF245BC45FBFEBAFA27" box="[144,291,1442,1465]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gargarans">
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB3FFF245BC45FBFEBAFA27" box="[144,291,1442,1465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602">M. gargarans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in the Museum Koenig, Bonn) endorses this (
<figureCitation id="0BD42A7EFFB3FFF2463145F8FCE0FA27" box="[797,889,1441,1465]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="4.[212,279,1198,1220]" captionTargetBox="[212,1172,168,1166]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[212,1172,168,1166]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 3. Megaselia crassipes male (synonym of M. gargarans), left face of anal tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4006322" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4006322/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602">Figure 3</figureCitation>
). Furthermore, it is evident that it is a specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB3FFF244CD459BFDF1FA47" baseAuthorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[481,616,1474,1497]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB3FFF244CD459BFDF1FA47" box="[481,616,1474,1497]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602">M. crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at the larger and darker end of the spectrum of variation in this species. Therefore, the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB3FFF247CA45BBFCE0FA67" box="[742,889,1506,1529]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gargarans">
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB3FFF247CA45BBFCE0FA67" box="[742,889,1506,1529]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602">M. gargarans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB3FFF2469845BBFBA0FA67" baseAuthorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[948,1081,1506,1529]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB3FFF2469845BBFBA0FA67" box="[948,1081,1506,1529]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602">M. crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is herewith formally proposed. 
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB3FFF244F4465BFDE2F987" authorityName="Disney and Durska" authorityYear="2011" box="[472,635,1537,1561]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="basiturgida">
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB3FFF244F4465BFDE2F987" box="[472,635,1537,1561]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602">M. basiturgida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from two similarly darker males, but which are not quite as large as the 
<typeStatus id="4C548859FFB3FFF24758467BFD4CF9A4" box="[628,725,1570,1594]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB3FFF247DA467BFC16F9A7" box="[758,911,1570,1593]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602">
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB3FFF247DA467BFC15F9A7" box="[758,908,1570,1593]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gargarans">M. gargarans</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Furthermore, the left hypandrial lobes of these two males are paler than usual. However, in every other respect, they lie within the ranges of variation for 
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB3FFF24787463BFCA0F9E7" box="[683,825,1634,1657]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602">
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB3FFF24787463BFCACF9E7" baseAuthorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[683,821,1634,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">M. crassipes</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Therefore, the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB3FFF2458046DBFED2F907" authorityName="Disney and Durska" authorityYear="2011" box="[172,331,1665,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="basiturgida">
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB3FFF2458046DBFED2F907" box="[172,331,1665,1689]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602">M. basiturgida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB3FFF244AA46DBFD95F907" baseAuthorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[390,524,1666,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB3FFF244AA46DBFD95F907" box="[390,524,1666,1689]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1602">M. crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also herewith formally proposed. Critical details of 
<taxonomicName id="54EF4D78FFB4FFF545F8455CFEC2FA82" baseAuthorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[212,347,1285,1308]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1603" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis id="A19BEAE9FFB4FFF545F8455CFEC2FA82" box="[212,347,1285,1308]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1603">M. crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are given in 
<figureCitation id="0BD42A7EFFB4FFF544CB455DFDF1FA82" box="[487,616,1284,1308]" captionStart-0="Figure 1" captionStart-1="Figure 2" captionStartId-0="2.[212,279,1298,1320]" captionStartId-1="3.[144,211,1067,1089]" captionTargetBox-0="[213,1171,169,1265]" captionTargetBox-1="[145,1103,169,1034]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[212,1172,168,1266]" captionTargetId-1="figure@3.[144,1104,168,1035]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="Figure 1. Megaselia crassipes male. (A) Posterior face of front tarsus; (B) left face of hypopytgium. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." captionText-1="Figure 2. Megaselia crassipes male (synonym of M. basiturgida). (A) Left face of hypopygium; (B) posterior face of front tibia and basitarsus. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4006316" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4006318" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/4006316/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/4006318/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1603">Figures 1â€“2</figureCitation>
and its recognition clarified in the revised couplets 79â€“81 of the key to the males recorded from the British Isles (
<bibRefCitation id="F77E4B0AFFB4FFF54655457DFB9BFAA2" author="Disney RHL" box="[889,1026,1316,1340]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1603" pagination="1 - 155" refId="ref8043" refString="Disney RHL. 1989. Scuttle Flies - Diptera Phoridae Genus Megaselia. Handbk Ident Br Insects. 10: 1 - 155." type="journal article" year="1989">Disney 1989</bibRefCitation>
) (see below).
</paragraph>
